                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Combs</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-03-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Loomis instructs Mr. Combs to protest-against the unfriendly action of the
                    Guatemalan Government in refusing to recognize the American citizenship of
                    Posadas, who was duly naturalized in the United States after a residence of
                    twelve years, and to ask for Posadas’ release.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
